<TITLE> Peelkhana SSC examinees sit maths </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 19 (bdnews24.com)Eight SSC examinees of families affected by the Peelkhana carnage were sitting for their mathematics paper at the Government Laboratory School on Thursday. Education minister Nurul Islam Nahid, visiting the examination centre, told reporters, "They are taking this examination under special arrangements for families who were affected by the mutiny." Professor Shamsul Haque, chairman of the Dhaka education board, told bdnews24.com, "The SSC examinees directly affected by the February 25-26 BDR massacre missed the scheduled exams for obvious reasons." "They were given the opportunity to take the maths paper today." "The normal HSC examination centre at Peelkhana has been shifted to Government Laboratory School and Udayan School." The education minister had announced in the wake of the mutiny that the examinees affected by the incident would be allowed to take the missed exams at a convenient date later. b
